  <!-- §9 What is an LED Neon Sign -->
  <h2 style="font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">What Is an LED Neon Sign with a Transparent Backboard?</h2>
  <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
    Traditional neon is made from glass tubes filled with neon gas. It requires high voltage, custom fabrication, and careful handling. This product is different: it uses LEDs (light-emitting diodes) mounted behind a transparent acrylic backboard.
  </p>
  <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
    The magic is in the backboard. When lit, the acrylic appears to glow, creating the illusion that the neon "floats" off the wall. It's a clever optical trick that captures the neon aesthetic without the fragility or cost.
  </p>
  <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
    <strong>Key differences from true neon:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.8;">
    <li>LEDs are durable and cool to the touch</li>
    <li>No glass tubes means no risk of breakage</li>
    <li>USB power vs. 110V or higher</li>
    <li>Preset designs only (no custom fabrication)</li>
    <li>Fraction of the cost ($49 vs. $200+)</li>
  </ul>
  <p style="line-height: 1.6;">
    If you love the neon look but don't need a one-of-a-kind design, this is the smart choice.
  </p>

