  <!-- §15 FAQ -->
  <div class="faq" style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Is this real neon?</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        No. Real neon uses glass tubes filled with neon gas and requires high voltage. This product uses LEDs mounted behind an acrylic backboard, which mimics the neon look at a fraction of the cost. The transparent backboard creates a convincing floating-neon illusion.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Can I customize the design or add my own text?</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        No. This product comes in 3 preset styles only. You cannot customize the design, add text, or request modifications. If you need a custom design, you'll need to order a true custom neon sign from a fabricator, which costs $200–500+.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">How bright is the light?</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        It's bright enough to set mood and create ambiance in a dark room. Not bright enough to read by or use as primary room lighting. Perfect for accent lighting, bedside vibes, or dorm ambiance. If you need functional lighting, pair it with other lamps.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Does it get hot? Is it safe around kids or pets?</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        LEDs run cool. After extended use (4+ hours), you might feel mild warmth, but nothing unsafe. You can touch it with bare hands. It's safe around children and pets. The acrylic is sturdy and won't shatter like glass neon.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">What does IP42 protection mean? Can I use it in a bathroom?</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        IP42 means it's dust-resistant and splash-resistant (like accidental water spray or light rain indoors). It's NOT waterproof. Do not install in bathrooms, kitchens, or outdoor areas. Stick to bedrooms, living rooms, offices, and dorms. A splash from a glass won't destroy it, but sustained moisture will.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">How long does it last? Will it burn out?</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        500,000 hours of operation. At 24/7 continuous use, that's roughly 57 years. For normal use (4–8 hours per day), it will outlive your interest in the design. Effectively permanent. You'll want to replace it for aesthetic reasons long before the LEDs fail.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">What are the power requirements and does it need a special outlet?</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        Standard AC outlet (100-240V, 50-60Hz). The sign draws minimal power (~5-10W depending on brightness and design). No special outlet, adapter, or installation required — plug and play.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Can I dim the brightness or change the color?</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        The brightness and color are fixed by design. You cannot dim it or change colors once purchased. The color scheme is determined by which preset design you select. Some variants may have a simple on/off switch; check your product listing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">How should I mount this on my wall?</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        Most neon-style LED signs come with adhesive strips or mounting brackets. Avoid drilling if using adhesive. For heavier signs (over 3 lbs), wall anchors or screws are recommended. Check your specific product for mounting hardware included.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Will this work in a large room or only small spaces?</h3>
      <p style="margin: 0; line-height: 1.6;">
        Neon-style LED wall decor is ambient accent lighting — it creates visual impact close-up and in direct line of sight. In a large room, you'll need to position it where it's visible. It won't brighten an entire room, but it will definitely catch eyes in a 10-15 foot radius.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

